  "body": "If state is currently:\n\n```\n{\n   foo: 123,\n   user: {typing: false, active: false}\n}\n```\n\nThen calling `this.setState({user: {typing: true}})` results in state being:\n\n```\n{\n   foo: 123,\n   user: {typing: true}\n}\n```\n\nIt would be great to have a `setStateRecursively` function and to make it clear in the `setState` documentation that it only merges one level deep before just replacing sub-states. \n",
